  "texts": [
    "Instructions:",
    "Read the question and the list of criteria carefully. 2.",
    "For each criterion, decide first whether it *makes a factual claim* -that is, whether it asserts something that can be verified as true or false in the real world.",
    "**Distinguishing referential vs. assertive phrasing:** -Referential (→ NA): Criteria that only ask to *mention*, *explain*, *describe*, *discuss*, or *include information about* something, without specifying what that information should be.",
    "These refer to factual topics but do not assert any particular fact."
  ]
